27 Oct 1940'></a></td><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=286'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_570d6d3cf03aa.jpg" border='0' alt='Broadside view of USS Wasp (Wasp-class) at anchor on 27 Dec 1940, probably in Guantanamo Bay, Cuba. Note F3F fighters and SB2U Vindicator aircraft on the flight deck.'></a></td><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=286'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_wasp24.jpg" border='0' alt='Lieutenant Harold Kelly (standing with pipe) and other officers playing cards aboard USS Wasp, date unknown'></a></td></tr></table><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=286'>See all 33 photographs of Aircraft Carrier USS Wasp (Wasp-class)</a><br /><br /><br /><br />
